nen und Figurenkonstellationen; Fragen der Deutung (insbesondere ‚Historizität‘ und Aktualisierbarkeit des heldenepischen Stoffes, Diskussion von Heldentum und Gewalt); die literarhistorische Einordnung als „Dichtung über Heldendichtung“.  aThe so-called ‘historical’ Dietrich epics, the thirteenth-century Middle High German heroic epics dealing with Dietrich von Bern (Verona), the corresponding saga of the Ostrogoth king Theoderic the Great, tells of Dietrich’s warring conflicts with his uncle Ermanaric to gain the rule of Northern Italy. The monograph elucidates the text group (the flight epics ‛Dietrich’s Flight’ and ‘The Battle of Ravenna’ and the associated epic ‛The Death of Alphart’) from the perspective of literary history.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEpic poetry, GermanxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman poetryyMiddle High German, 1050-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aHeldensage. 4aAlpharts Tod. 4aDietrich (von Bern). 4aDietrichs Flucht. 4aHeldendichtung. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aRabenschlacht. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aDietrich (von Bern).  aHeroic Epic.  aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2010z9783110233605oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012z97831103011680 cprintz978311025131940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025132640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110251326423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110251326/original 